{
  "message": "fuzz(repair-codec): 21 structured seeds across encode\u00d7decode phase space\n\nExisting 8 seeds left the codec roundtrip's parameter matrix\nsparsely covered. Add 21 seeds spanning:\n\n  block_size \u00d7 source_block_count \u00d7 repair_count:\n    * bs \u2208 {64, 128, 256}\n    * k \u2208 {1, 2, 3, 4, 8} (single-block edge through max)\n    * repair_count \u2208 {0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 8} (none / partial / full)\n\n  decode capacity boundaries:\n    * corrupt_count = 0 (no decode work)\n    * corrupt_count < repair_count (under capacity, must recover)\n    * corrupt_count == repair_count (at capacity boundary)\n    * corrupt_count > repair_count (over capacity, no recovery promised)\n    * corrupt_count == k (recovery assertion gracefully skipped)\n\n  repair-symbol mutation modes (mutation_mode = b%4):\n    * mode 1: truncate one symbol payload (incl. new_len = 0)\n    * mode 2: truncate the symbol list (keep = 0 / 1 / repair_count)\n    * mode 3: XOR-flip a byte in one symbol\n\nCross-coverage:\n    * unique 16-byte UUID and offset (first_block != 0) seeds\n    * single-block edge: k=1, r=1, with and without corruption\n\nValidation: -runs=0 corpus replay clean across 29 entries; partial\nfuzz run grew corpus 30\u219237 with no crashes (slow exec_s on\nbs=256 k=8 ASAN-instrumented seeds).",
